<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="52" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1440,584,829]" pageId="8" pageNumber="52">Putative synapomorphies:—basal leaf single, pentangular in transverse section; tunic reticulate, fibrous, fibrous-papery; inflorescence umbellate; filament glabrous; tepals yellow adaxially, acuminate to long acuminate at the apex, hardened and enlarged after anthesis.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
